nd those concerned with the history of law. The book is within the reach of an advanced undergraduate and graduate audience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aConstitutional historyxTo 146 B.CxGreecexAthens. 0aConstitutional historyzGreecezAthensyTo 146 B.C. 0aCourtsxGreecexAthens. 0aCourtszGreecezAthens. 0aDroit constitutionnelxGrècexAthènes. 0aRule of lawxGreecexAthens. 0aRule of lawzGreecezAthens. 0aRègle de droitxGrèce. 0aTribunauxxGrècexAthènes. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Greece.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311074526940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271072920zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271072920423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780271072920.jpg  a978-3-11-074526-9  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK